<item>
            <title>[SOLR-15650] Picking lucene defType in Solr Admin doesn&apos;t actually pass defType=lucene through</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-15650</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Noticed that Solr Admin assumes that you don&apos;t have a defType defined.&#160; If you pick lucene from the defType dropdown, we actually don&apos;t pass it in, so if you have defined a default defType like edismax or dismax, then THAT is what is actually run.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This PR follows some of the other dropdowns in that if you don&apos;t make a selection, the dropdown has a -------, and then you run whatever defualt you have, otherwise, if you pick lucene, then we pass it in!&lt;/p&gt;</description>
